      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "JILLIBY AURA (2) is a talented filly who won fresh in Victoria before a close second in the NSW Oaks last start. That was her third Group 1 placing having also mixed it with the top fillies south of the border last season. Draws well so looks tough to stop. ALDEBARAN ADA (3) hasn't been too far off JILLIBY AURA in her two starts so far this campaign and was beaten only 2m when third in the Oaks. She draws outside that filly so it won't be easy to turn the tables but she should perform well again. HALLEBESOFINE (5) was first up for more than five months when beaten less than 8m after racing parked in the Oaks. Draws lower so could progress off that. DESIRING DIAMONDS (4) has trialled well since breaking last start and is a chance based on a third when resuming at Menangle two back.",
